19 "§1338. Transfer of cases
20 A. All pending cases filed in the Civil District Court for the Parish parish
21 of Orleans over civil commitment proceedings where the Criminal District Court for
22 the Parish parish of Orleans has determined a mentally defective defendant is
23 incapable of standing trial, is a danger to himself or others, and is unlikely in the
24 foreseeable future to be capable of standing trial are hereby transferred to the
25 Criminal District Court for the Parish of Orleans for further proceedings in
26 accordance with law. A judge of the civil district court or the criminal district court
27 on his own motion, or upon motion by the district attorney of Orleans Parish or the
28 attorney of the defendant, may have such case transferred upon the signing of the
29 order to transfer by either a judge of the Criminal District Court for the Parish parish
30 of Orleans or a judge of the Civil District Court for the Parish parish of Orleans.
31 Upon the signing of such an order, the clerk of the Civil District Court for the Parish
32 of Orleans or the clerk of the Criminal District Court for the Parish of Orleans shall
33 effect delivery of the record to the clerk of the Criminal District Court for the Parish
34 of Orleans, who shall receipt the same and properly file it in his office. The Criminal
35 District Court for the Parish parish of Orleans shall hear and dispose of the case with
36 the same legal effect as if it had been instituted in that court in the first instance.
37 B. With respect to cases and jurisdiction transferred according to this
38 Section, the criminal sheriff for the parish of Orleans is vested with the power and
39 authority to serve all notices, subpoenas, papers, writs, and orders and to make
40 proper return thereto to the Criminal District Court for the Parish parish of Orleans.
